# 🔐 ISMS Learning Project — ISO/IEC 27001:2022

## ⚠️ Note

This project was developed as part of my learning process in ISO/IEC 27001.

It is based on a case study and used for educational purposes to understand how an Information Security Management System (ISMS) works in practice.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates the application of ISO/IEC 27001 concepts, focusing on understanding how organizations manage information security risks.

The content includes key steps of ISMS implementation such as context analysis, scope definition, and risk management.

---

## 🧠 Concepts Covered

- Context Analysis (Clause 4.1)
- Interested Parties (Clause 4.2)
- Scope of the ISMS (Clause 4.3)
- ISMS Structure (Clause 4.4)
- Risk Assessment and Treatment
- Security Controls (Annex A)
- PDCA Cycle (Plan, Do, Check, Act)

---

## 📦 Scope (Example)

The ISMS scope includes:

- ERP system (SAP S/4HANA)
- CRM system (Salesforce)
- PLM system
- Cloud infrastructure (AWS and Microsoft Azure)
- On-premises data centers

Excluded from scope:

- Third-party systems not directly controlled by the organization

---

## ⚠️ Key Risks Identified

- Exposure of sensitive data
- System vulnerabilities
- Lack of monitoring and logging
- Dependency on cloud services

---

## 🛠️ Risk Treatment Approach

- Implementation of access control
- Use of encryption
- System updates and patch management
- Monitoring and logging mechanisms

---

## 🔄 PDCA Cycle

- **Plan:** Identify risks and define controls  
- **Do:** Implement security measures  
- **Check:** Monitor and evaluate performance  
- **Act:** Improve continuously  

---

## 🎯 Purpose

The goal of this project is to build practical knowledge in Cybersecurity and GRC, focusing on ISO/IEC 27001.

